    <p class="section-number">08, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Frigidaire jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Two representative service calls, model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Frigidaire service across each environment.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Frigidaire FFTR2021TB top-freezer, Rancho Cucamonga</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Ice maker producing very little ice, ice cubes hollow and small. Owner had recently replaced the water filter; symptoms persisted.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Mineral buildup in the ice maker fill tube and on the water inlet valve screens, the Inland Empire's harder water profile is the typical driver. Ice maker module itself tested OK; valve solenoid coils ohms-out within spec but flow rate at the fill tube was 35% below target.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Descaled the fill tube, cleaned valve screens, verified normal water flow rate at the ice maker. No parts replacement needed. Counseled owner on water filter replacement timing and recommended a whole-house softener evaluation given the broader hard-water symptoms.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $89 diagnostic only, no parts cost. 60 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Frigidaire FFFW4033QW front-load washer, Sherman Oaks</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> E20 error displayed at end of every wash cycle. Customer had checked the obvious filter and didn't find debris.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Filter recheck confirmed clean. Drain pump amp draw measured 30% above spec, early-stage failure of the pump itself, just barely managing to drain on most cycles before the E20 timeout. Pump impeller showed visible wear on inspection.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Drain pump replacement with OEM Frigidaire part (in stock on the truck). Verified normal drain cycle time and E20 cleared on full cycle test.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $295 total. Same-day, completed on the diagnostic visit in 70 minutes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

